# Benchmark Papers for Underwater Object Detection

This folder contains benchmark papers used as references and baselines for the implementation of **underwater object detection** with WaterNet and YOLOv7. These papers provide the foundational concepts, methods, and performance metrics used in the project.

## üìÑ **Benchmark Papers**

### 1. **Modern Replication of WaterNet**
- **Title**: "An Underwater Image Enhancement Benchmark Dataset and Beyond"
- **Publication**: IEEE Transactions on Image Processing (TIP), 2019
- **Authors**: Xiaojie Guo, Zhan Ma, Haibo Li
- **Description**: 
  This paper introduces WaterNet, a state-of-the-art underwater image enhancement model. The method focuses on improving underwater image quality by addressing issues like turbidity, low contrast, and color distortions. It also provides an underwater image benchmark dataset.
- **Key Contributions**:
  - Proposed WaterNet for enhancing underwater image quality.
  - Released a benchmark dataset for evaluating underwater image enhancement methods.
- **Link**: [IEEE Xplore](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/8917818/)

### 2. **YOLOv7**
- **Title**: "YOLOv7: Trainable Bag-of-Freebies Sets New State-of-the-Art for Real-Time Object Detectors"
- **Publication**: IEEE, 2022
- **Authors**: Chien-Yao Wang, Alexey Bochkovskiy, Hong-Yuan Mark Liao
- **Description**: 
  YOLOv7 introduces a novel real-time object detection framework with high accuracy and efficiency. The paper sets new standards for object detection performance, making it a strong candidate for underwater object detection tasks.
- **Key Contributions**:
  - Introduced novel techniques like Extended Efficient Layer Aggregation Networks (E-ELAN).
  - Achieved state-of-the-art results on various object detection benchmarks.
- **Link**: [IEEE Xplore](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10204762/)

